text.section:
A unit may not adopt a rule or regulation or take any other administrative action that would result in expenditures in excess of the limitations in the State budget unless:
the General Assembly expressly approves the administrative action;
if the General Assembly is not in session, the President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of Delegates:
consult with the Joint Audit Committee; and
after receiving the written advice of the Joint Audit Committee, jointly give written approval for the administrative action; or
the Governor declares, by proclamation, that the administrative action is necessary and a matter of emergency.
